WEBVTT

00:00.967 --> 00:03.033
♪ WHEN THIS BOY MEETS WORLD ♪

00:03.033 --> 00:06.000
♪ BOY MEETS WORLD ♪

00:06.000 --> 00:10.367
♪ WANDERIN' DOWN THIS ROAD
THAT WE CALL LIFE ♪

00:10.367 --> 00:12.667
♪ IS WHAT WE'RE DOIN' ♪

00:12.667 --> 00:14.500
♪ IT'S GOOD TO KNOW
I HAVE FRIENDS ♪

00:14.500 --> 00:16.300
♪ WHO WILL ALWAYS ♪

00:16.300 --> 00:18.734
♪ STAND BY ME ♪

00:18.734 --> 00:21.800
♪ WHEN THIS BOY MEETS WORLD ♪

00:21.800 --> 00:23.667
<i>PREVIOUSLY </i>
<i>ON "BOY MEETS WORLD" -- </i>

00:23.667 --> 00:26.100
TO CORY AND TOPANGA!

00:26.100 --> 00:28.734
All: CORY AND TOPANGA!

00:28.734 --> 00:33.734
AND NOW...
I WOULD LIKE TO GIVE MY GIFT

00:33.734 --> 00:37.400
TO MY LITTLE BROTHER
AND NEW SISTER-IN-LAW.

00:37.400 --> 00:41.000
ERIC, THIS WEDDING
WAS MORE THAN ENOUGH.

00:41.000 --> 00:42.600
YEAH, IT WAS, WASN'T IT?

00:42.600 --> 00:45.734
BUT I DO HAVE
ONE MORE THING UP MY SLEEVE.

00:45.734 --> 00:48.400
I HOLD IN MY HAND A KEY --

00:48.400 --> 00:51.233
A KEY TO THE HONEYMOON SUITE

00:51.233 --> 00:53.967
OF THE PHILADELPHIA
VICTORIA HOTEL.

00:53.967 --> 00:55.667
SO THAT AFTER THIS --

00:55.667 --> 00:57.233
BYE!

00:57.233 --> 00:59.200
WHOO!
BYE!

00:59.200 --> 01:01.133
ALL RIGHT!

01:06.000 --> 01:07.500
SO, YOU THINK
WE'RE FINALLY READY

01:07.500 --> 01:08.700
TO BE MR.
AND MRS. MATTHEWS?

01:08.700 --> 01:11.233
I THINK WE'VE BEEN READY
OUR WHOLE LIVES.

01:11.233 --> 01:12.233
WHOO!

01:16.100 --> 01:19.133
YOU STAY THERE!

01:19.133 --> 01:20.900
CORY, DON'T YOU WANT TO...

01:20.900 --> 01:22.900
EXPLORE...

01:22.900 --> 01:24.100
AND TAKE OUR TIME?
WHY?

01:24.100 --> 01:27.200
THERE'S SUCH A THING
AS FOREPLAY.

01:27.200 --> 01:28.300
DON'T NEED IT.

01:28.300 --> 01:29.867
WELL, MAYBE I MIGHT.

01:29.867 --> 01:32.000
YOU'VE HAD 12 YEARS OF IT.
HOW MUCH MORE DO YOU REQUIRE?

01:32.000 --> 01:33.467
JUST WAIT RIGHT HERE.

01:33.467 --> 01:35.600
I'M SURE YOU
WON'T BE DISAPPOINTED.

01:35.600 --> 01:37.667
NO! NO!
DON'T LEAVE ME!

01:37.667 --> 01:39.667
I CAN'T DO THIS ALONE!

01:39.667 --> 01:41.900
OH, SHE'S GONE.

01:41.900 --> 01:43.800
WHAT'LL I DO?

01:43.800 --> 01:46.000
I'LL EAT FRUIT.

01:50.400 --> 01:54.300
"THANK YOU FOR CHOOSING
THE PHILADELPHIA VICTORIAN

01:54.300 --> 01:55.934
FOR YOUR WEDDING."

01:55.934 --> 01:57.500
ISN'T THAT NICE?

01:57.500 --> 02:01.200
"CONGRATULATIONS TO THE NEW
MR. AND MRS. HAROLD PETERMAN."

02:03.734 --> 02:05.200
WELL, NORMALLY,

02:05.200 --> 02:07.200
MY INQUISITIVE NATURE
WOULD TAKE OVER AT THIS POINT.

02:07.200 --> 02:08.567
HOWEVER...

02:12.233 --> 02:14.400
YAI-YAI-YAI!

02:21.767 --> 02:24.600
OH!

02:24.600 --> 02:26.467
[ Laughing ] OH, MY!

02:26.467 --> 02:27.467
OH HO HO!

02:27.467 --> 02:29.300
THIS IS SO GREAT!

02:29.300 --> 02:31.767
I WISH SHAWN WAS HERE!

02:31.767 --> 02:33.867
I THINK IT'S BETTER
THAT WE'RE ALONE.

02:33.867 --> 02:35.600
YES.

02:35.600 --> 02:36.767
THAT'S IT.

02:36.767 --> 02:39.033
THAT'S IT?

02:39.033 --> 02:41.600
THERE'S NOTHING
UNDER THESE COVERS BUT ME.

02:41.600 --> 02:46.000
I HAVE BEEN WAITING
FOR THIS MOMENT MY ENTIRE LIFE!

02:46.000 --> 02:49.967
YAY! HO HO HO!
OH HO HO HO HO!

02:49.967 --> 02:52.133
AND ONLY FOR YOU.

02:52.133 --> 02:53.700
[ GASPING ]

02:56.000 --> 02:58.000
OH, TOPANGA, I LOVE YOU.

02:58.000 --> 03:00.400
I LOVE YOU
AND I LOVE ERIC.

03:00.400 --> 03:01.500
WHAT?

03:01.500 --> 03:04.300
THIS BEAUTIFUL WEDDING
HE ARRANGED

03:04.300 --> 03:07.600
MAKES UP FOR EVERYTHING BAD
HE'S EVER DONE TO US.

03:07.600 --> 03:09.000
I LOVE YOU.

03:09.000 --> 03:10.667
I LOVE YOU.

03:10.667 --> 03:12.100
POLICE!

03:12.100 --> 03:14.367
YOU'RE KIDDING.

03:14.367 --> 03:15.834
ROLL AWAY FROM THE LADY

03:15.834 --> 03:17.667
AND PUT YOUR HANDS
WHERE I CAN SEE 'EM.

03:17.667 --> 03:19.500
NO! KILL ME!

03:19.500 --> 03:21.000
[ GRUNTS ]

03:21.000 --> 03:23.000
WHY ARE YOU GUYS
DOING THIS?

03:23.000 --> 03:24.600
ARE YOU
MRS. HAROLD PETERMAN?

03:24.600 --> 03:25.600
NO!

03:25.600 --> 03:26.667
THAT'S WHY.

03:26.667 --> 03:28.600
AW, FELLAS,
THIS WAS MY WEDDING DAY.

03:28.600 --> 03:30.734
CAN'T YOU COME BACK
IN TWO MINUTES?!

03:30.734 --> 03:31.967
PLEASE?!

03:31.967 --> 03:35.300
HELP! ERIC!
HELP!

03:35.300 --> 03:37.300
COR, HOW COOL
IS THIS, MAN?

03:37.300 --> 03:40.300
[ Scottish accent ] WE GET
TO GO IN THE PADDY WAGON!

03:40.300 --> 03:41.900
[ Imitating siren ]
WOO-OOH, WOO-OOH, WOO-OOH!

03:41.900 --> 03:44.200
LET'S GO, FUN BOY!
COME ON, COME ON!

03:44.200 --> 03:46.000
CAN I USE YOUR NIGHTSTICK?

04:01.100 --> 04:02.400
SO, ARE YOU EXCITED?

04:02.400 --> 04:04.300
WE'RE FINALLY
ON OUR HONEYMOON!

04:04.300 --> 04:06.000
YOU GONNA CARRY ME
OVER THE THRESHOLD?

04:06.000 --> 04:08.467
NO, BECAUSE
THE LAST TIME I DID,

04:08.467 --> 04:09.800
THE POLICE BROKE IN

04:09.800 --> 04:12.300
AND I SPENT THE NIGHT
WITH A GUY NAMED SHEILA.

04:12.300 --> 04:14.400
OKAY,
THEN LET'S JUST GO IN.

04:14.400 --> 04:16.200
NUH-UH.

04:16.200 --> 04:17.867
YOU WANT ME TO CARRY <i>YOU?  </i>

04:17.867 --> 04:20.000
I'M LIGHT AS A FEATHER,
REALLY.

04:20.000 --> 04:22.367
[ GRUNTS ]

04:22.367 --> 04:23.700
UGH!

04:23.700 --> 04:26.400
UGH!

04:26.400 --> 04:28.600
HAVE YOUR WAY WITH ME NOW.

04:30.867 --> 04:33.767
Cory: YAY!

04:39.300 --> 04:41.200
Man: <i>ATTENTION KATONKA GUESTS -- </i>

04:41.200 --> 04:44.700
<i>WILL THE COUPLE WHO LEFT </i>
<i>THEIR DOG IN THE PIRANHA TANK </i>

04:44.700 --> 04:46.567
<i>PLEASE COME CLAIM HIS COLLAR? </i>

04:46.567 --> 04:48.300
IS THIS SEAT TAKEN, DEAR?

04:48.300 --> 04:51.367
ACTUALLY, I WAS SAVING IT
FOR MY HUSBAND, CORY --

04:51.367 --> 04:52.600
CORY MATTHEWS.

04:52.600 --> 04:55.100
I'M MRS. MATTHEWS.
THAT'S MY NAME NOW.

04:55.100 --> 04:57.367
HE'S MY HUSBAND.
I'M HIS WIFE.

04:57.367 --> 04:59.133
ON YOUR HONEYMOON, DEAR?

04:59.133 --> 05:00.600
I'M A WIFE!

05:00.600 --> 05:04.000
ME TOO.
MADELINE NELSON.

05:04.000 --> 05:07.967
I USED TO BE
MADELINE PIGSNIFFLE.

05:07.967 --> 05:10.000
THAT'S WHY I GOT MARRIED.

05:10.000 --> 05:15.567
I GOT MARRIED BECAUSE
I'M CRAZY ABOUT MY MAN.

05:15.567 --> 05:17.300
HONEYMOON, YES.

05:19.500 --> 05:21.500
LAST NIGHT WAS
OUR FIRST NIGHT TOGETHER

05:21.500 --> 05:22.800
AS MAN AND WIFE.

05:22.800 --> 05:24.800
HE STILL SLEEPING?

05:24.800 --> 05:27.600
OH, YEAH.
I WORE HIM OUT.

05:29.300 --> 05:31.100
ATTAGIRL.

05:31.100 --> 05:32.400
MINE'S SLEEPING, AS WELL.

05:32.400 --> 05:33.967
YOU WORE HIM OUT, TOO?

05:33.967 --> 05:35.834
YES, GRADUALLY.

05:37.033 --> 05:39.400
YOU KNOW,
WE HONEYMOONED HERE OURSELVES.

05:39.400 --> 05:40.967
IT'S PARADISE HERE,
ISN'T IT?

05:40.967 --> 05:43.467
WE COME BACK EVERY YEAR
ON OUR ANNIVERSARY,

05:43.467 --> 05:45.133
BUT THIS YEAR
IS VERY SPECIAL

05:45.133 --> 05:47.400
BECAUSE WE'VE DECIDED
TO RETIRE HERE.

05:47.400 --> 05:51.300
<i>PAGING MRS. MATTHEWS, </i>
<i>MRS. CORY MATTHEWS. </i>

05:51.300 --> 05:53.567
THAT'S ME! THAT'S ME!

05:55.400 --> 05:57.767
HA HA HA HA HA!

05:57.767 --> 05:59.000
HONEYMOON?

05:59.000 --> 06:00.066
HOW CAN YOU TELL?

06:00.066 --> 06:02.767
I CAN SEE ALL YOUR TEETH.

06:02.767 --> 06:04.233
IT'S TRUE.
I'M A MAN NOW.

06:04.233 --> 06:05.600
YOU SEEM
PRETTY HAPPY, BOY.

06:05.600 --> 06:07.000
I WAS AN ANIMAL,
MISTER.

06:07.000 --> 06:08.567
IT'S GOOD IN
THE BEGINNING, ISN'T IT?

06:08.567 --> 06:09.867
IT'S MY NEW
FAVORITE THING.

06:10.934 --> 06:12.100
HI, MR. MATTHEWS.

06:12.100 --> 06:13.400
HI, MRS. MATTHEWS.

06:13.400 --> 06:14.867
MINE.

06:15.934 --> 06:17.000
MINE.

06:17.000 --> 06:18.367
DID YOU GET MY PAGE?

06:18.367 --> 06:19.900
I TOLD THEM TO PAGE YOU,

06:19.900 --> 06:22.967
THEN I TOLD THEM
TO PAGE DR. CHOCOLATE PUDDING.

06:22.967 --> 06:24.400
THAT WAS FUN.

06:24.400 --> 06:25.767
CORY, THIS IS MRS. NELSON.

06:25.767 --> 06:28.367
SHE AND HER HUSBAND
HAVE DECIDED TO RETIRE HERE.

06:28.367 --> 06:30.100
OH, GOSH,
THAT MUST BE AMAZING.

06:30.100 --> 06:32.567
EVERYTHING ON THIS ISLAND
IS JUST AMAZING.

06:32.567 --> 06:34.200
WHAT'S IT LIKE
TO LIVE IN PARADISE?

06:34.200 --> 06:36.100
AMAZING.
AMAZING.

06:36.100 --> 06:39.400
THIS IS THE SOFTEST TOWEL
THAT HAS EVER GRACED MY TUSHIE.

06:39.400 --> 06:41.367
WAIT TILL YOU DRINK
THE WATER.

06:41.367 --> 06:42.667
IT TASTES LIKE CANDY.

06:42.667 --> 06:44.300
YOU GUYS ARE SO LUCKY
TO BE HERE.

06:44.300 --> 06:46.967
IF WE WEREN'T HERE,
WE WOULD BE SITTING AT HOME

06:46.967 --> 06:49.100
IN PHILADELPHIA,
IN MR. FEENY'S CLASS.

06:49.100 --> 06:50.734
IT'S PROBABLY SNOWING
THERE.

06:50.734 --> 06:53.400
AND THE SANITATION DEPARTMENT
IS PROBABLY ON STRIKE.

06:53.400 --> 06:56.667
WE'D BE IN BALTIMORE, WATCHING
OUR GRANDSON JOEY'S SOCCER TEAM.

06:56.667 --> 06:58.300
THE MIGHTY GOPHERS.

06:58.300 --> 07:01.233
SHE WOULD BE IN THE CAR
WITH THE HEATER GOING, SAYING,

07:01.233 --> 07:03.100
"IS IT OVER YET?
I'M SO COLD!"

07:03.100 --> 07:04.400
I DON'T LIKE THE COLD.

07:04.400 --> 07:05.500
ME NEITHER.

07:05.500 --> 07:07.767
IN FACT,
I'M COLD RIGHT NOW.

07:07.767 --> 07:09.200
CORY, IT'S 92 DEGREES.

07:09.200 --> 07:10.367
I'M VERY COLD.

07:10.367 --> 07:12.000
WHY DON'T WE
GO IN THE BEDROOM

07:12.000 --> 07:14.767
AND GO UNDER THE COVERS
LIKE WE DID BEFORE?

07:14.767 --> 07:16.367
CORY, WE'RE MARRIED NOW.

07:16.367 --> 07:20.000
WE CAN DO IT EVERY NIGHT
FOR THE REST OF YOUR LIFE.

07:20.000 --> 07:24.033
GET IT IN WRITING, KID.

07:24.033 --> 07:25.700
<i>DR. PUDDING. </i>

07:25.700 --> 07:28.600
<i>PAGING DR. CHOCOLATE PUDDING. </i>

07:28.600 --> 07:32.000
OH, I LOVE THIS PLACE!

07:42.867 --> 07:44.734
[ Gasping ] OH! OH!

07:44.734 --> 07:49.133
I AM SO FREAKIN' HOT.

07:49.133 --> 07:51.467
HONEYMOON, DAY TWO.

07:51.467 --> 07:53.700
CONTINUING DUTIES AS BEST MAN.

07:53.700 --> 07:55.367
SCREWED UP WEDDING NIGHT,

07:55.367 --> 07:58.300
SO MUST MAKE IT UP TO THEM
HERE IN PARADISE.

07:58.300 --> 08:00.567
BOY, IT'S <i>HOT. </i>

08:00.567 --> 08:04.600
I AM LOSING MY TRAIN OF THOUGHT.

08:04.600 --> 08:09.233
I HAVE DECIDED TO PASS OUT.

08:18.600 --> 08:20.834
MMM.

08:20.834 --> 08:23.500
THAT WAS A VERY ROMANTIC
THING TO DO.

08:23.500 --> 08:26.400
THIS IS THE MOST ROMANTIC PLACE
THERE COULD EVER BE.

08:26.400 --> 08:29.000
YOU WANNA DANCE?

08:29.000 --> 08:31.100
SINCE WHEN
DO YOU LIKE TO DANCE?

08:31.100 --> 08:33.800
SINCE I'M IN THE MOST BEAUTIFUL
PLACE IN THE WORLD,

08:33.800 --> 08:36.667
STARING AT THE MOST BEAUTIFUL
WOMAN I HAVE EVER SEEN.

08:39.400 --> 08:41.200
BUT THERE'S NO MUSIC.

08:41.200 --> 08:43.500
WELL, WE'RE IN PARADISE,
TOPANGA.

08:43.500 --> 08:44.867
WE'LL MAKE OUR OWN.

08:44.867 --> 08:47.467
[ SLOW DANCE MUSIC PLAYS ]

08:49.800 --> 08:51.200
WOW!

08:55.734 --> 09:00.367
ALL RIGHT, HOW IS IT THIS HOT
WHEN THERE'S NO SUN OUT?

09:00.367 --> 09:01.600
ARE YOU HOT?!

09:01.600 --> 09:02.967
ARE YOU HOT?!

09:02.967 --> 09:04.834
ARE YOU HOT?!

09:04.834 --> 09:06.400
NAH.

09:06.400 --> 09:08.100
CORY, I AM SO RELAXED HERE.

09:08.100 --> 09:11.000
THIS PLACE LETS ME
FORGET ABOUT EVERYTHING.

09:11.000 --> 09:13.133
IT'S SO UNSPOILED HERE,
YOU KNOW.

09:13.133 --> 09:14.800
IT'S LIKE TIME HAS STOPPED.

09:14.800 --> 09:18.400
DO YOU REMEMBER THOSE CUTE
THATCHED HUTS ON THE BEACH?

09:18.400 --> 09:20.467
YOU KNOW, I SAW
THIS OLD FISHERMAN

09:20.467 --> 09:22.700
MAKING A FLUTE
OUT OF A BAMBOO REED.

09:22.700 --> 09:24.867
AND THERE WAS HARDLY ANY LINE
AT STARBUCKS.

09:24.867 --> 09:26.600
YOU KNOW WHAT?

09:26.600 --> 09:29.000
THAT'S IT.
WE'RE STAYIN' HERE.

09:29.000 --> 09:30.600
WE CAN STAY A FEW MORE DAYS?

09:30.600 --> 09:33.000
A FEW MORE DAYS HERE,
NO RESPONSIBILITIES,

09:33.000 --> 09:35.000
NO FEENY, NO CRAZY ERIC.

09:38.934 --> 09:41.600
YEAH, LET'S STAY
A FEW MORE DAYS.

09:41.600 --> 09:43.700
LET'S STAY A FEW MORE DAYS.

09:43.700 --> 09:47.367
IN FACT, LET'S NEVER GO HOME.

09:47.367 --> 09:49.767
RIGHT,
LET'S JUST NEVER GO HOME.

09:49.767 --> 09:51.000
I'M NOT KIDDING.

09:51.000 --> 09:52.800
UH-OH.

09:52.800 --> 09:54.667
SERIOUSLY, GIVE ME
ONE GOOD REASON

09:54.667 --> 09:56.000
WHY WE SHOULDN'T STAY HERE.

09:56.000 --> 09:57.600
WHY SHOULD WE GO HOME?

09:57.600 --> 10:00.967
BECAUSE
IT'S WHERE OUR HOME IS.

10:00.967 --> 10:04.000
NOT IF WE STAY HERE
FOR THE REST OF OUR LIVES.

10:10.133 --> 10:11.667
TOPANGA, WE'RE IN PARADISE.

10:11.667 --> 10:13.400
LET'S NEVER GO HOME.

10:13.400 --> 10:16.200
CORY, GET REAL.
WE CAN'T STAY HERE.

10:16.200 --> 10:17.567
FINE, IS THAT WHAT YOU WANT?

10:17.567 --> 10:19.500
LET'S JUST GO BACK
TO PHILADELPHIA

10:19.500 --> 10:21.734
AND SPEND OUR YOUTH
BREATHING POLLUTION

10:21.734 --> 10:23.700
AND HAVING TO BOW DOWN
TO THE MAN

10:23.700 --> 10:25.100
AND THEN COME BACK HERE

10:25.100 --> 10:27.600
WHEN WE'RE TOO OLD
TO WIN THE LIMBO CONTEST.

10:27.600 --> 10:30.767
IS THAT WHAT YOU WANT,
TOPANGA -- TO NOT WIN?

10:30.767 --> 10:32.667
NO, I'D REALLY LIKE
TO WIN.

10:32.667 --> 10:33.734
GOOD.

10:33.734 --> 10:36.834
TOPANGA,
LOOK OUT THERE!

10:36.834 --> 10:38.100
[ SPLASH ]

10:40.233 --> 10:42.834
IMAGINE WAKING UP TO THAT
EVERY SINGLE DAY

10:42.834 --> 10:44.467
FOR THE REST OF YOUR LIFE.

10:44.467 --> 10:46.367
I THINK SOMEONE
WAS ON THE BALCONY.

10:46.367 --> 10:47.867
WHO CARES?

10:47.867 --> 10:50.367
LISTEN, TOPANGA,
DON'T YOU WANNA STAY?

10:50.367 --> 10:52.800
NOBODY STAYS ON VACATION
FOREVER.

10:52.800 --> 10:54.100
THE NELSONS DO.

10:54.100 --> 10:57.734
TELL ME HOW WE'RE GOING TO
MAKE A LIVING.

10:57.734 --> 10:59.500
PARADISE IS EXPENSIVE.
DID YOU THINK ABOUT THAT?

10:59.500 --> 11:01.400
YOU THINK I HAVEN'T THOUGHT
ABOUT THAT?

11:01.400 --> 11:03.033
YOU THINK I'M NOT
A REALIST?

11:03.033 --> 11:08.834
YOU THINK I HAVEN'T THOUGHT
OF LITTLE CORY JR. AND BARBARA?

11:08.834 --> 11:10.300
STEVEN AND CHLOE.

11:10.300 --> 11:13.300
OOH, THOSE ARE NICE.

11:13.300 --> 11:16.100
LET'S MAKE 'EM!

11:16.100 --> 11:18.133
HOW ABOUT WE MAKE
A <i>LIVING </i>FIRST?

11:18.133 --> 11:20.667
HOW DO WE DO THAT?

11:20.667 --> 11:23.567
YOU THINK I HAVEN'T CONSIDERED
OUR LIVING SITUATION?

11:23.567 --> 11:25.867
YOU THINK THIS IS WHIMSY?
THIS IS NOT WHIMSY.

11:25.867 --> 11:28.767
THIS IS OUR FUTURE, BABY.

11:30.834 --> 11:31.934
A COCONUT?

11:31.934 --> 11:35.000
Oh, yeah.

11:39.000 --> 11:41.400
[ Harshly ] HELLO!

11:41.400 --> 11:42.834
[ LAUGHING ]

11:42.834 --> 11:44.367
THIS IS DAVID LETTERMAN.

11:44.367 --> 11:46.100
[ Nasal voice ]
AND I'M JAY LENO.

11:46.100 --> 11:47.400
I'M EDGY.

11:47.400 --> 11:49.300
I'M NOT.

11:49.300 --> 11:52.300
AND HERE'S OUR GUEST,
ARNOLD SCHWARZENEGGER!

11:53.567 --> 11:56.000
[ Austrian accent ]
HELLO, HOW ARE YOU?

11:56.000 --> 11:59.200
I'M THE "COCO-NATOR."

11:59.200 --> 12:01.467
[ Normal voice ]
THANK YOU!

12:01.467 --> 12:03.800
THANK YOU SO MUCH!

12:03.800 --> 12:05.400
YOU'RE WONDERFUL,
YOU'RE WONDERFUL!

12:05.400 --> 12:06.767
GUESS WHERE I'VE BEEN.

12:06.767 --> 12:07.767
SHOPPIN'?

12:07.767 --> 12:09.467
WE ARE A TOTAL SUCCESS
OVERNIGHT!

12:09.467 --> 12:11.967
I TOOK OUT A BANK ACCOUNT
AT KATONKA SAVINGS AND LOAN.

12:11.967 --> 12:13.967
I TOOK OUT AN AD
IN <i>THE KATONKA TIMES, </i>

12:13.967 --> 12:16.100
AND I STILL HAD TIME
TO CATCH THIS FISH.

12:16.100 --> 12:17.567
AH, WHAT A WOMAN!

12:17.567 --> 12:20.800
JUST THINK, ALL THAT TIME
WITH FEENY WASTED

12:20.800 --> 12:23.667
WHEN MY REAL SUCCESS
WAS RIGHT HERE.

12:23.667 --> 12:25.233
BECAUSE I AM...

12:25.233 --> 12:28.233
THE COCONUT GUY!

12:28.233 --> 12:30.300
HEY, YOU'RE THE WIFE
OF THE COCONUT GUY!

12:30.300 --> 12:31.767
YES, I AM!

12:34.867 --> 12:36.600
HEH HEH HEH!
MRS. NELSON!

12:36.600 --> 12:38.200
WHAT CAN I CARVE FOR YOU?

12:38.200 --> 12:39.900
YOU RUN THIS PLACE?

12:39.900 --> 12:42.000
WE DECIDED TO STAY HERE
LIKE YOU GUYS.

12:42.000 --> 12:42.934
YOU CONVINCED US.

12:44.133 --> 12:46.300
I BOUGHT THIS ENTIRE OUTFIT
FOR THREE BANANAS.

12:46.300 --> 12:47.600
THAT CONVINCED ME.

12:47.600 --> 12:49.767
AH, DARN IT.
I'M OUT OF POOKA SHELLS.

12:49.767 --> 12:50.967
WIFE TOPANGA,

12:50.967 --> 12:53.800
COULD YOU RUN
TO THE "SHELL" STATION?

12:53.800 --> 12:57.767
[ Giggling ] YOU KNOW,
YOU'RE FUNNIER IN PARADISE.

12:57.767 --> 12:59.967
OH, FRANK, GUESS WHAT.

12:59.967 --> 13:01.967
THE MATTHEWS
HAVE DECIDED TO MOVE HERE.

13:01.967 --> 13:03.967
WELL, WELCOME TO PARADISE!

13:03.967 --> 13:05.834
<i>MUKA TOKA, </i>BABY.

13:05.834 --> 13:08.400
<i>MUKA TOKA </i>BACK AT YOU!

13:08.400 --> 13:09.800
WHAT CAN I CARVE FOR YOU?

13:09.800 --> 13:12.133
A NICE REGIS PHILBIN?
HIS LOVELY WIFE, JOY?

13:12.133 --> 13:14.734
COULD YOU MAKE ME
A COCONUT SOCCER PLAYER?

13:14.734 --> 13:16.300
LOOK, WE HEARD FROM JOEY.

13:16.300 --> 13:17.300
YOUR GRANDSON?

13:17.300 --> 13:18.400
THEY WON.

13:18.400 --> 13:20.867
THE MIGHTY GOPHERS
MADE THE PLAYOFFS?

13:20.867 --> 13:22.934
EIGHT YEARS WE WATCHED
THAT KID STINK,

13:22.934 --> 13:24.734
AND THE MINUTE WE LEAVE,
HE'S PELé.

13:25.834 --> 13:27.100
WE'LL CALL.

13:27.100 --> 13:30.100
RIGHT. WE'LL CALL
AND WE'LL WISH HIM LUCK.

13:30.100 --> 13:31.567
DARN IT!

13:31.567 --> 13:35.233
I FORGOT TO HAVE TOPANGA PICK ME
UP SOME OF THEM GOOGLY EYES.

13:48.400 --> 13:50.367
HONEYMOON, DAY SIX.

13:50.367 --> 13:53.500
WHEN THEY DECIDED TO LIVE HERE,
I THOUGHT THE NEWLYWEDS

13:53.500 --> 13:55.867
HAD CAUGHT A BAD CASE
OF ISLAND FEVER.

13:55.867 --> 13:58.133
BUT IT TURNS OUT
THEY'VE ADJUSTED WELL

13:58.133 --> 13:59.500
TO LIFE IN THIS PLACE,

13:59.500 --> 14:01.667
AND I DON'T REALLY KNOW
WHAT TO DO.

14:01.667 --> 14:04.000
LOOK, IRV, THIS ONE TALKS!

14:04.000 --> 14:05.000
OH, NO.

14:05.000 --> 14:06.767
COCONUTS
DON'T TALK, GLADYS.

14:06.767 --> 14:08.100
I HEARD HIM.

14:08.100 --> 14:09.600
ALL RIGHT.

14:09.600 --> 14:12.734
SMASH IT OPEN
WITH A HAMMER.

14:12.734 --> 14:15.600
HOW ABOUT I SMASH <i>YOU  </i>
OPEN WITH A HAMMER?!

14:15.600 --> 14:17.100
AAAAAAH!

14:17.100 --> 14:19.233
RUN, GLADYS!

14:21.667 --> 14:25.400
YOU BELIEVE THAT?

14:33.834 --> 14:35.767
GOOD MORNING, FADOOKIE!

14:37.200 --> 14:38.500
GOOD MORNING, BAVOOKIE!

14:41.033 --> 14:42.133
GOOD MORNING, OOKIE!

14:42.133 --> 14:44.133
OH, CORY, MRS. CORY,

14:44.133 --> 14:47.800
YOU TWO
ARE THE TALK OF THE ISLAND.

14:47.800 --> 14:49.700
REALLY, OOKIE?
I HOPE IT'S GOOD.

14:49.700 --> 14:51.233
OH, VERY GOOD.

14:51.233 --> 14:53.300
YES!
VERY GOOD!
VERY GOOD!

14:53.300 --> 14:56.300
WE THINK YOU ARE KATONKA'S
FAVORITE FUN COUPLE.

14:56.300 --> 14:57.834
WE'RE VERY IMPRESSED

14:57.834 --> 15:00.834
WITH HOW QUICKLY YOU'VE
ACCLIMATED TO OUR CUSTOMS.

15:00.834 --> 15:02.000
WELL...

15:02.000 --> 15:05.800
I'M STILL HAVING TROUBLE
USING SOUP AS DEODORANT.

15:05.800 --> 15:08.667
ANYWAY, WE HAVE AN ELECTION
FOR MAYOR COMING UP,

15:08.667 --> 15:11.800
AND WE'D REALLY LIKE YOU
TO CONSIDER RUNNING FOR OFFICE,

15:11.800 --> 15:15.200
REPRESENTING
OUR MOOKIE-TIMBALA PARTY.

15:15.200 --> 15:16.500
WHO'S THE OTHER PARTY?

15:16.500 --> 15:17.600
COMMUNISTS.

15:18.734 --> 15:20.600
THIS IS
OUR MOST IMPORTANT ELECTION

15:20.600 --> 15:22.834
SINCE OUR PEOPLE MOVED HERE
FROM OHIO.

15:22.834 --> 15:25.667
THEY WANT ME
TO BE MAYOR OF PARADISE!

15:27.100 --> 15:28.100
HEY.

15:28.100 --> 15:29.567
YOU TWO ARE DRESSED UP.

15:29.567 --> 15:33.100
HEY-HEY, GUYS, THEY WANT ME
TO BE MAYOR OF PARADISE!

15:33.100 --> 15:35.133
I'M GONNA BE
MAYOR McCOCONUT!

15:35.133 --> 15:36.367
FRANK...

15:36.367 --> 15:38.400
YOU WANNA BE
MY CAMPAIGN MANAGER?

15:38.400 --> 15:39.934
They'll bring in
the old vote

15:39.934 --> 15:42.567
like it was early-bird dinner
at Lawakwa's.

15:42.567 --> 15:45.133
WE'VE BEEN LOOKING FOR YOU
TO SAY THAT WE'RE LEAVING.

15:45.133 --> 15:46.133
YOU'RE LEAVING?

15:46.133 --> 15:47.967
OUR GRANDSON JOEY CALLED US.

15:47.967 --> 15:49.100
SO?

15:49.100 --> 15:51.000
THE MIGHTY GOPHERS
MADE THE FINALS.

15:51.000 --> 15:52.200
SO?

15:52.200 --> 15:54.767
SO I AM GOING TO SIT
AND BE COLD IN THE CAR.

15:54.767 --> 15:56.500
HOW COULD WE MISS IT?

15:56.500 --> 15:58.500
BUT YOU GUYS
ARE COMING BACK, RIGHT?

16:00.066 --> 16:01.200
GOODBYE, KIDS.

16:01.200 --> 16:03.000
HAVE A NICE LIFE,
SON.

16:03.000 --> 16:04.600
HOW COULD WE NOT?

16:04.600 --> 16:06.000
WE'RE IN PARADISE.

16:12.300 --> 16:15.800
HONEYMOON, DAY 12.

16:15.800 --> 16:17.667
WHAT IS PARADISE?

16:17.667 --> 16:21.700
HAVE HUNCH
IS MORE THAN SAND AND WATER.

16:21.700 --> 16:24.200
WANT TO HELP SISTER
AND NEW BROTHER-IN-LAW,

16:24.200 --> 16:26.934
BUT DON'T KNOW WHAT'S BEST.

16:26.934 --> 16:29.000
WHAT DO YOU THINK, MR. BIRD?

16:30.934 --> 16:32.767
AAH!

16:32.767 --> 16:35.500
[ Slurring ]
BIRD BIT ME.

16:35.500 --> 16:40.233
LEFT SIDE...PARALYZED.

16:40.233 --> 16:44.200
POSSIBLE BAD SIGN.

16:44.200 --> 16:46.667
[ GROANS ]

16:56.200 --> 17:00.834
CORY...HONEY...

17:00.834 --> 17:03.600
YOU'VE BEEN HERE ALL NIGHT.
COME TO BED.

17:03.600 --> 17:05.667
YOU USED TO LIKE THAT.

17:05.667 --> 17:08.200
SORRY, I WAS JUST FINISHING
THIS SOCCER PLAYER

17:08.200 --> 17:10.000
FOR THE NELSONS.

17:10.000 --> 17:13.467
THIS ISN'T
A SOCCER PLAYER.

17:13.467 --> 17:14.767
WHAT?

17:14.767 --> 17:17.400
THIS IS SHAWN.

17:17.400 --> 17:20.500
THIS ISN'T SHAWN.

17:20.500 --> 17:22.967
THIS IS...

17:22.967 --> 17:25.600
SHAWN.

17:25.600 --> 17:27.400
WHY'D I DO THAT?

17:27.400 --> 17:29.867
I CAN'T EVEN REMEMBER
DOING THAT.

17:29.867 --> 17:32.734
WHO'S THIS ONE
SUPPOSED TO BE?

17:32.734 --> 17:35.600
THAT'S, UH...

17:35.600 --> 17:37.233
CAP'N CRUNCH.

17:37.233 --> 17:38.667
NO, IT'S NOT.

17:38.667 --> 17:41.000
WELL, THEN
WHO ELSE COULD IT BE?

17:41.000 --> 17:45.000
WELL, IT COULD BE
MR. FEENY.

17:45.000 --> 17:48.133
CORY, WHY WOULD YOU
STAY UP ALL NIGHT

17:48.133 --> 17:51.100
MAKING A SHAWN
AND A MR. FEENY?

17:51.100 --> 17:53.000
I DON'T KNOW,
I DON'T KNOW.

17:53.000 --> 17:55.667
I CAN'T REMEMBER
DOING THAT ONE, EITHER.

17:55.667 --> 17:58.200
CORY...

17:58.200 --> 18:00.900
YEAH.

18:00.900 --> 18:04.200
I MISS THEM, TOO.

18:04.200 --> 18:09.567
BOY, IT'S HOT HERE
ALL OF A SUDDEN, ISN'T IT?

18:09.567 --> 18:11.867
ISN'T IT HOT?

18:11.867 --> 18:14.734
YEAH, IT'S HOT.

18:22.300 --> 18:24.200
[ DOOR OPENS ]

18:24.200 --> 18:25.600
HEY!
HEY!
HEY!
HEY!

18:25.600 --> 18:28.300
THE NEWLYWEDS!
HOW WAS THE TRIP?

18:28.300 --> 18:29.367
GREAT.

18:29.367 --> 18:30.600
ALMOST
DIDN'T COME HOME.

18:30.600 --> 18:32.467
WHAT DID YOU BRING ME?

18:32.467 --> 18:33.767
NOTHING.

18:33.767 --> 18:37.033
WELCOME HOME,
MR. AND MRS. MATTHEWS.

18:37.033 --> 18:39.200
NOW IT'S OFFICIAL.

18:39.200 --> 18:41.567
I EXPECT TO SEE YOU
IN CLASS TOMORROW.

18:41.567 --> 18:44.600
MAKING UP 12 DAYS OF LECTURES
WILL BE NO EASY TASK,

18:44.600 --> 18:46.300
ESPECIALLY
THE WAY I TEACH.

18:46.300 --> 18:48.300
MANY NUANCES, YOU KNOW.

18:48.300 --> 18:50.300
YOU'LL NEVER KNOW
HOW MUCH WE MISSED YOU.

18:50.300 --> 18:52.233
YOU'LL NEVER KNOW
HOW MUCH WE MISSED <i>YOU.  </i>

18:52.233 --> 18:53.934
COME ON,
WHAT DID YOU BRING ME?!

18:53.934 --> 18:55.200
NOTHING.

18:55.200 --> 18:57.100
SO, HOW WAS
THE HONEYMOON?

18:57.100 --> 18:59.133
DID YOU EVER LEAVE
THE ROOM?

18:59.133 --> 19:00.233
YEAH, WE LEFT.

19:00.233 --> 19:01.834
BUT THEN WE CAME BACK.

19:01.834 --> 19:03.300
WHAT DID IT LOOK LIKE?

19:03.300 --> 19:04.500
IT WAS BEAUTIFUL.

19:04.500 --> 19:06.567
OH, TELL US ABOUT IT.

19:06.567 --> 19:09.934
RIGHT ABOUT NOW, WE'D BE SITTIN'
WITH OUR FEET IN THE SAND

19:09.934 --> 19:11.467
AND WATCHIN' THE SUN SET.

19:11.467 --> 19:14.667
HAVIN' DINNER BETWEEN THESE
TWO GORGEOUS LITTLE PALM TREES,

19:14.667 --> 19:16.567
STARIN' OUT AT THE OCEAN.

19:16.567 --> 19:19.367
WOW.
IT SOUNDS LIKE PARADISE.

19:24.867 --> 19:26.100
ALMOST.

19:31.500 --> 19:33.600
DIDN'T EVEN HAVE TO FINISH
THE COCONUTS

19:33.600 --> 19:36.767
OF MOM, DAD, ME, AND MORGAN
FOR CORY AND TOPANGA TO REALIZE

19:36.767 --> 19:38.200
WHERE PARADISE REALLY IS.

19:38.200 --> 19:39.667
GOOD FOR THEM.

19:39.667 --> 19:42.967
FOR ME, PARADISE IS A PLACE
I'VE FOUND THE BEST PART

19:42.967 --> 19:44.734
OF BEING THE BEST MAN.

19:44.734 --> 19:47.934
MMM!
MMM!
MMM!
MMM!

19:47.934 --> 19:49.667
AHH!

19:49.667 --> 19:51.600
10 MORE MINUTES, MAN.

19:51.600 --> 19:53.500
MMM!
MMM!
MMM!
